    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 1991 Porsche 911 Carrera 2 is a superlative example of the 964 generation, featuring the air-cooled 3.6-liter M64 flat-six engine. The powerplant exhibits exceptional mechanical sympathy, with recent top-end service ensuring perfect valve clearances and leak-free cylinder heads. Power is delivered through the G50 five-speed transaxle, renowned for its precise synchromesh and robust torque handling. The chassis remains factory-correct, retaining its MacPherson strut front and semi-trailing arm rear suspension, providing the communicative feedback and rear-biased weight distribution characteristic of the marque. Every body panel displays original factory tolerances and VIN stickers, while the Brembo-sourced four-piston calipers provide fade-free deceleration. This is a benchmark-quality specimen for the discerning collector.",
